title: The Ben Simmons Saga Continues and Klutch Sports Group Remains in the Spotlight | Group Chat
description: Justin, Rob, and Wos are back to discuss the situation in Philadelphia

title: Are the Warriors Back? Inside the Title Race and Potential Trades With Marcus Thompson
description: The Athletic writer joins KOC to discuss what Golden State will look like this year

title: How This Week's Patrick Beverley Trades Explain the NBA
description:
Chris Ryan is joined by The Ringer's Rob Mahoney to discuss Patrick Beverley getting traded twice 
  in a week. Then they discuss the financial and competitive realities of several teams around the league.

title: S8E13 - Epilogue: The Life of Pablo
description:
Yeezus brought Kanye to the church steps with his divine woman. But what happened after the vows were 
  exhanged? That's the journey of The Life of Pablo.

title: S8E12 - Finale: The YEEZUS Tour
description:
In our Season 8 finale, we dissect the narrative and stage design of Kanye West's 2013 Yeezus Tour. 
  In this five act show, Kanye uses songs from his entire catalog to mythologize his life.

title: BONUS - Yeezus Song Draft w/ Travis Bean & Chris Lambert
description:
Cole sits down with S8 co-writers Travis Bean and Chris Lambert for a first ever "Song Draft -- an 
  NBA-style draft of the songs on Kanye West's Yeezus.

title: The New Look Bulls & Retooling Contenders ft. HoopsRaeven | Dishes & Dimes
description:
Raeven is back to talk about NBA free agent signings we liked and disliked. How do these 
  BUlls fit together? Are the Lakers still the favorite in the West? Which signings were 
  head scratchers?

title: The Milwaukee Bucks, 2021 NBA Champions ft. @HoopsRaeven | Dishes & Dimes
description:
Raeven is back to talk about the end to the 2021 NBA season, the champion Bucks, 
  Giannis' rise as the best player in the league, and more!

title: Are the Suns Inevitable Champs? ft. @HoopsRaeven | Dishes & Dimes
description:
Raeven is here to talk all things NBA Finals, how the Suns were able to go up 
  2-0, what is wrong with the Bucks stars, and what they need to go back in this 
  series.

title: Most Intriguing NBA Finals Storylines
description:
We're finally back at the NBA Finals. Here are some storylines to look out for 
  as we watch some new stars take the stage!

title: CP3's Redemption Tour, Brook Lopez aka the Bucks' Savior ft. HoopsRaeven | Dishes & Dimes
description:
Raeven is back to talk about the Suns' journey to the finals, Game 5 of the ECF, and what 
  we will remember about this year's playoffs!

title: Potential NBA Finals Storylines | Dishes & Dimes
description:
Christian goes into the storylines and narratives of the final four teams left in this year's 
  playoffs. The 2018 Draft, the Clippers' and Hawks' first taste of the finals, and is Giannis 
  lucky?

title: S1E11 - Drama by Dave
description:
We've reached the end of Dave's theraputic journey, his Psychodrama. So where 
  does this journey leave us? "Drama" is an emotional, spiritual finale, featuring 
  the voice of Dave's brother Chris, recorded from prison. Hosted by Kayo Chingonyi.

title: S1E10 - Voices by Dave
description:
For the penultimate track of his era-defining debut album, Dave calls on the 
  sound palette of UK Garage - a musical style born before he was - to bring a 
  sugary hit of dopamine to Psychodrama's last throes. Hosted by Kayo Chingonyi.

title: S1E9 - Lesley by Dave (feat. Ruelle)
description:
The next episode on this series of Decode delves into an 11-minute storytelling 
  epic. Track 9 "Lesley" takes on themes of domestic violence, mental health and 
  betrayal, featuring the haunting and cinematic voices of Ruelle. Hosted by 
  Kayo Chingonyi.

title: Drake: 'Take Care' | Vol. 1 Ep. 15
description:
On the Volume 1 finale, Jinx and Shea discuss Drake's sophomore album, 
  "Take Care". They discuss which track deserves the title of Best Song 
  among "Take Care", "Marvin's Room", "Look What You've Done", "Headlines", 
  and others.

title: Clipse: 'Lord Willin'' | Vol. 1 Ep. 14
description:
On the second-to-last episode of Volume 1, Kinx and Shea discuss 'Lord 
  Willin'', the debut studio album by rap duo Clipse. They talk about how the Virginia 
  brothers Pusha T and Malice teamed up with the Neptunes to create classics like, 
  "Grindin'", "When The Last Time", and "Cot Damn."

title: Ms. Lauryn Hill: 'The Miseducation of Lauryn Hill' | Vol. 1 Ep. 13
description:
Jinx and Shea discuss the holy grail: Ms. Lauryn Hill's Diamond-certified, 
  multi-Grammy Award-winning solo studio album, 'The Miseducation of Lauryn 
  Hill'. They talk about how she left the Grammy Award-winning group Fugees to 
  create hits like "To Zion", "Doo-Wop", and "Ex-Factor".
